history.content: I wouldn't recommend doing 162 and 189 and a breadth next semester. Somewhat based on the grades and workloads you listed, but because you seem to have other fundamental classes to take (if you got a B+ in 16B which would be 2 years ago, you should certainly take EE127 or Math 110 or something next semester; 189 pretty much boils down to linalg, probability maturity is far less important than linalg skills) and it looks like you have Sp20 to take 189 (which will also be with better profs than in fall).

children.subject: As long as you spend time on the homeworks and read the notes your past performance, you should be fine based on your past performance. For reference I also got a B+ in 16B, took 189 2 years later with 3 techs in the fall and did fairly well in the class.
